tables.description: The departments table represents the organizational structure of the company, storing information about each department, including its name, location, and manager. This table typically stores records of all departments within the company, making it a crucial component in HR and organizational analytics. By analyzing this table, business users can gain insights into the company's structure and make informed decisions about resource allocation and departmental performance.

columns.description: The dept_id column represents a unique identifier for each department, allowing for efficient data retrieval and analysis. This column stores integer values, making it suitable for indexing and aggregation operations. By analyzing this column, business users can gain insights into departmental structure and performance.

The dept_name column stores the name of each department, providing valuable information about the company's organizational structure. This column stores character varying values, making it suitable for text analysis and search operations. By analyzing this column, business users can gain insights into departmental roles and responsibilities.

The location_id column represents a foreign key referencing the locations table, linking each department to its corresponding location. This column stores integer values, making it suitable for joining and aggregation operations. By analyzing this column, business users can gain insights into departmental locations and logistics.

The manager_name column stores the name of the manager responsible for each department, providing valuable information about the company's leadership structure. This column stores character varying values, making it suitable for text analysis and search operations. By analyzing this column, business users can gain insights into departmental management and leadership.

The created_at column stores the creation date of each department, providing valuable information about the company's organizational history. This column stores timestamp values, making it suitable for time-series analysis and reporting operations. By analyzing this column, business users can gain insights into departmental creation and evolution.

tables.description: The employees table stores information about each employee, including their name, department, job title, and hire date. This table is essential for HR and payroll operations, as well as for analytics related to employee demographics, job roles, and career progression. By analyzing this table, business users can gain insights into the company's workforce and make informed decisions about talent management and employee development.

columns.description: The emp_id column represents a unique identifier for each employee, allowing for efficient data retrieval and analysis. The emp_name column stores the name of each employee, providing valuable information about the company's workforce. This column stores character varying values, making it suitable for text analysis and search operations. By analyzing this column, business users can gain insights into employee demographics and performance.

The dept_id column represents a foreign key referencing the departments table, linking each employee to their corresponding department. The job_title column stores the job title of each employee, providing valuable information about the company's job roles and responsibilities. The hire_date column stores the hire date of each employee, providing valuable information about the company's workforce history. tables.description: The incidents table represents a record of all incidents that have occurred within the company, including the employee involved, the incident date, type, and severity. This table is critical for risk management and compliance, as well as for analytics related to employee safety and well-being. By analyzing this table, business users can identify trends and patterns in incidents and take proactive measures to prevent future occurrences.

The severity column stores the severity level of each incident, providing valuable information about the company's risk management and compliance.
